@statement

What is the value of $f(x)$ at $x=1$?


@hint
Don't be scared! Just plug it in!


@solution

$$
\frac{1^2 - 1}{1-1} = \frac{0}{0}.
$$
 However, we can't divide by $0$. So, $f(x)$ must not be defined at $x=1$.
